property.name: text
property.value:
This model is based on the F-14 Longitudinal Flight Control model (f14.mdl) from Matlab. The composite actor NzPilotG uses the d/dt actor (derivative).
The Aircraft Model provides the vertical velocity w and the pitch rate q. The Angle of Attack alpha and the pitch rate q as well as the stick pitch command sent by the pilot are used by the AutoPilot (the analogous controller) to command the Elevator Deflector of the aircraft.
The pilot g force indicates the stresses on the pilot (that can be destructive).
